{{Orphan|date=September 2017}}
{{Taxobox | image_caption = | regnum = [[Animal]]ia | phylum = [[Arthropod]]a | classis = [[Insect]]a | ordo = [[Lepidoptera]] | subordo = [[Glossata]] | familia = '''Aenigmatineidae''' | genus = '''''Aenigmatinea''''' | genus_authority = Kristensen & Edwards, 2015 | species = '''''A. glatzella''''' | binomial = ''Aenigmatinea glatzella'' | binomial_authority = Kristensen & Edwards, 2015 }}
'''Aenigmatineidae''' is a family of [[basal (phylogeny)|basal]] [[Lepidoptera]], [[moth]]s discovered on [[Kangaroo Island]] in [[South Australia]]. The family is based on a single species discovered in 2015, '''''Aenigmatinea glatzella''''', commonly known as the "enigma moth".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-03-04/enigma-moth-from-kangaroo-island-helps-with-evolutionary-puzzle/6277908 |date=9 March 2015 |title=Enigma moth from Kangaroo Island helps scientists unravel evolutionary puzzle of tiny tongues |last=Maher |first=Louise |website=ABC News |publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation}}</ref> The larvae feed on conifers by mining the stem of ''[[Callitris]]'' plants in the [[cypress]] family. The adult has highly reduced mouthparts but its position in the [[Glossata]] containing the more familiar moths-with-tongues is confirmed by morphological and DNA sequence similarity. The group is best treated as a sister of the family [[Neopseustidae]].<ref name=desc>{{cite journal|last1= Kristensen|first1=Niels P. |last2= Hilton|first2=Douglas J. |last3= Kallies|first3=Axel |last4= Milla|first4=Liz |last5= Rota|first5=Jadranka |last6= Wahlberg|first6=Niklas |last7= Wilcox|first7=Stephen A. |last8= Glatz|first8=Richard v. |last9= Young|first9= David A. |last10= Cocking|first10= Glenn |last11= Edwards|first11= Ted |last12= Gibbs|first12= George W. |last13= Halsey|first13= Mike|title= A new extant family of primitive moths from Kangaroo Island, Australia, and its significance for understanding early Lepidoptera evolution |journal=Systematic Entomology|volume=40|issue=1|pages=5–16|year=2015|doi=10.1111/syen.12115}}</ref>
