[[File:Amaryllis belladonna sfbg 2.jpg|thumb|''[[Amaryllis belladonna]]'']] '''Amaryllidoideae''' ('''Amaryllidaceae ''s.s.''''', '''amaryllids''') is a subfamily of [[monocot]] [[flowering plant]]s in the [[Family (biology)|family]] [[Amaryllidaceae]], [[Order (biology)|order]] [[Asparagales]]. The subfamily includes about seventy [[genus|genera]], with over eight hundred [[species]], and a worldwide distribution.
The [[Amaryllidoideae]] subfamily includes about 70 [[genera]].{{sfn|Stevens|2016|loc=[http://www.mobot.org/mobot/research/apweb/orders/asparagalesweb.htm#Amaryllidoideae Amaryllidoideae]}}
